_README_CONTENT = f"""{_VX_TITLE}  —  Quick Reference
===================================
by Vider_06  |  github.com/Vider06/V0rtex

A single-file Windows malware analysis platform (Python + Tkinter).
No external launcher needed. Run: python v0rtex.py
All data is stored locally in V0rtex_System/ — no telemetry, no cloud.

1. Add API keys -> CFG tab -> API KEYS
   Supported: VirusTotal · MalwareBazaar · AbuseIPDB · URLScan
              AlienVault OTX · Shodan · GreyNoise · HybridAnalysis
   Free VirusTotal key: 500 requests/day. Get one at virustotal.com.

2. Download YARA rules -> YARA tab -> LIBRARY
   Select repos (Neo23x0, Elastic, Avast, etc.) -> click DOWNLOAD
   Rules compile on first scan — expect ~60s delay the first time.

3. Exclude the install folder from Windows Defender
   Done automatically by setup. If YARA still fails, do it manually:
   Windows Security -> Virus & threat protection -> Exclusions -> Add folder

  + Add File       Scan a single file (drag & drop onto the window also works)
  Add Folder       Recursively queue all files in a folder
  Scan URL         Submit a URL to VirusTotal for reputation check
  AutoScan         Watch a folder — auto-scans any new file dropped in it
  Sandbox          Launch a file inside a monitored watcher environment

Each scan pipeline: SHA256 hash -> YARA match -> PE header parse -> VirusTotal API
Results appear in HOME -> DASHBOARD (recent scans table) and LOGS tab.
A full HTML + JSON report is saved in V0rtex_System/reports/ for every scan.

HOME      Dashboard · recent scans table · quick action buttons · system health
LOGS      File operation log (left) + debug log (right)
CHRT      Charts: bar chart of scan results · entropy histogram · threat heatmap
          Heatmap: rows = threat category, columns = file type, cell = count.
          Dark red = many files in that combination. Useful to spot patterns.
REP       Browse / open / delete HTML · JSON · TXT scan reports
IOC       IOC extractor · MITRE ATT&CK mapper · threat feeds · IP/domain rep
YARA      Scan files with YARA · download community rules · rule editor · deobfuscator
PERF      Live CPU / RAM / disk / network monitor (requires psutil)
TL        Chronological scan history chart — spot scan volume over time
SB        Auto-scan watcher · Process sandbox monitor · File analyzer · Strings tab
SETUP     Re-run install steps · repair packages · verify installation health
WD        Independent folder watcher — logs file create / modify / delete events
CFG       API keys · Config editor · Whitelist · Export · Checkpoints · DB browser
LOOK      Hash lookup · HEX viewer · Regex tester · Doc analyzer · Sig verifier ·
          Archive inspector · Macro extractor · B64 · XOR · BCONV · JWT · ROT ·
          PE header parser · Unicode inspector · Binary pattern search
PROC      Running processes · Services · Startup items · Env vars · Handles · Process tree
NET       Active connections · URL tools · IP/Domain reputation · DNS · WHOIS ·
          HTTP headers · SSL/TLS inspector · Port scanner · PCAP capture (tshark)
NOTES     Free notepad · MITRE ATT&CK matrix · TODO list · Code snippets
SET       Interface · Scan behaviour · Privacy · Paths · Network · Defense engine ·
          Notifications · Advanced settings (GC mode, crash handler, UAC elevation)
PROT      Build/destroy protected environment · Folder protection · Integrity check ·
          Defense engine config · Self-defense rules · Backup & restore
CRYPT     Encrypt / Decrypt files (AES-256-GCM) · Inspect encrypted blobs ·
          Hash calculator · Vigenère cipher
DZ        Danger Zone — full reset · secure wipe · system diagnostics · DB vacuum

The Recovery UI launches automatically when V0RTEX detects a broken install
(missing files, corrupt config, failed imports). You can also open it manually
from SET tab -> Advanced -> Open Recovery UI.

What it can do:
├─ Recreate Critical Files     Rebuilds config.json, scan_history.db,
│                               rules/ and reports/ folders from scratch.
│                               Use this if the app crashes immediately on start.
│
├─ Reset config.json           Wipes config.json back to factory defaults.
│                               All API keys and custom settings will be lost.
│                               Use if you get a KeyError or JSON parse error.
│
├─ Install / Repair Packages   Runs pip install for all required dependencies:
│                               yara-python · psutil · requests · watchdog ·
│                               fpdf2 · pefile · matplotlib · pillow · pystray
│                               Run this if any module import fails on startup.
│
├─ Rebuild YARA Index          Rescans the rules/ folder and rebuilds the
│                               compiled rule cache. Use if YARA shows 0 rules
│                               loaded even after downloading them.
│
├─ Clear Scan Database         Deletes all records from scan_history.db.
│                               Reports on disk are NOT deleted.
│                               Use if the DB is corrupt (sqlite3 errors in log).
│
├─ Wipe Debug Logs             Deletes all files in debug_log/ and crash_log.txt.
│
└─ Full Reinstall              Removes V0rtex_System/ entirely and re-runs setup.
                                Last resort — use only if everything else fails.

After any Recovery action, always restart V0RTEX completely (close and reopen).
The Recovery UI runs in a minimal environment independent of the main app,
so it works even when the main window cannot open at all.

Window closes immediately    -> run: python v0rtex.py from a terminal to see error
                               then: Recovery UI -> Recreate Critical Files
YARA loads 0 rules           -> Recovery UI -> Rebuild YARA Index
                               or: winget install Microsoft.VisualStudio.2022.BuildTools
YARA compile error           -> AV deleted yara-python — add folder to Defender exclusions
KeyError / JSON error        -> Recovery UI -> Reset config.json
VirusTotal returns nothing   -> CFG -> API KEYS: check key is valid (free = 500 req/day)
tshark / PCAP not working    -> install Wireshark from wireshark.org, add to PATH
High RAM on startup          -> YARA background compile running — wait ~60s
AV deletes modules           -> Windows Security -> Exclusions -> add V0rtex_System folder
App stuck on "SETUP"         -> close, delete V0rtex_System/setup_done.flag, restart
Charts show no data          -> run at least one scan first, then click Refresh
Heatmap is empty             -> no scan history yet — scan some files first
Dashboard shows nothing      -> click the ↻ button in the RECENT SCANS header

Drag & drop files            -> queues them for scan immediately
Double-click scan row        -> opens the full HTML report in browser
Right-click process row      -> context menu: send to YARA / kill process
Scroll wheel                 -> scrolls the active panel in any tab
Ctrl+click YARA rule         -> opens rule file in the editor

Backups saved to: V0rtex_backups/ (one level above V0rtex_System/)
Auto-backup runs at every session start (keeps last 5 backups).
Manual backup: PROT tab -> Backup -> Create Backup Now.
To restore: PROT tab -> Backup -> select snapshot -> Restore.
A restored backup requires a full app restart to take effect.

V0rtex_System/
├─ config.json          API keys, scan settings, UI preferences
├─ scan_history.db      SQLite database of all scan results
├─ reports/             Per-scan HTML + JSON + TXT reports
├─ rules/               YARA rule files (organised by source repo)
├─ quarantine/          Quarantined files (XOR-obfuscated, .quar extension)
├─ debug_log/           Crash reports and session logs
└─ backups/             Session checkpoint backups

VirusTotal (free)    500 lookups/day · 4 req/minute · MD5/SHA1/SHA256/URL
MalwareBazaar        No key needed for basic queries · 1000 req/day
AbuseIPDB            Free key: 1000 req/day · IP reputation
URLScan.io           Free key: submit URLs for full page analysis
AlienVault OTX       Free key: IOC feeds, pulse subscriptions
Shodan               Free key: limited host search · paid for full scan
GreyNoise            Free community key: IP noise/scan classification
HybridAnalysis       Free key: sandbox file submission + report retrieval

GitHub: https://github.com/Vider06/V0rtex
License: Copyright © 2024-2025 Vider_06 — All rights reserved
"""
_readme_txt.config(state="normal")
